<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><generator uri="https://jekyllrb.com/" version="4.4.1">Jekyll</generator><link href="https://darusik.github.io/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml"/><link href="https://darusik.github.io/" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/><updated>2026-04-09T14:22:18+00:00</updated><id>https://darusik.github.io/feed.xml</id><title type="html">Daryna Oliynyk</title><subtitle>PhD student in machine learning security at Vienna University of Technology. </subtitle><entry><title type="html">2nd place at the European Cybersecurity &amp;amp; AI Hackathon Championship</title><link href="https://darusik.github.io/blog/2025/european-cybersecurity-ai-hackathon/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="2nd place at the European Cybersecurity &amp;amp; AI Hackathon Championship"/><published>2025-12-14T12:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2025-12-14T12:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://darusik.github.io/blog/2025/european-cybersecurity-ai-hackathon</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://darusik.github.io/blog/2025/european-cybersecurity-ai-hackathon/"><![CDATA[<p>Last weekend I joined my colleagues Tanja Sarcevic, Yelyzaveta Klysa, and Sabina Khazari at the Trustworthy AI Hackathon in Vienna, organized by CISPA Helmholtz Center for Information Security.</p> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/highlights/hackathon-2025-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/highlights/hackathon-2025-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/highlights/hackathon-2025-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="/assets/img/highlights/hackathon-2025.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" alt="Our team with certificates at the European Cybersecurity and AI Hackathon Championship" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> <figcaption class="caption">Our team after winning second place.</figcaption> </figure> <p>Out of 16 teams, we finished 2nd and advanced to the championship grand final in St. Ingbert, Germany.</p> <p>More details about the event are available on the <a href="https://cispa.de/en/cispa-hackathon-championship">official CISPA Hackathon Championship page</a>.</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="highlights"/><category term="hackathon"/><category term="ml-security"/><category term="cispa"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[We finished 2nd in Vienna and advanced to the CISPA championship grand final.]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Invited talk at ESSAI 2025</title><link href="https://darusik.github.io/blog/2025/essai-talk/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Invited talk at ESSAI 2025"/><published>2025-11-20T12:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2025-11-20T12:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://darusik.github.io/blog/2025/essai-talk</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://darusik.github.io/blog/2025/essai-talk/"><![CDATA[<p>I was invited to speak at the European Symposium on Security and AI (ESSAI) in Rennes, France.</p> <p>I presented our joint SaTML 2025 paper, <em>Attackers Can Do Better: Over- and Understated Factors of Model Stealing Attacks</em>, co-authored with Rudolf Mayer and Andreas Rauber.</p> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/highlights/essai-2025-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/highlights/essai-2025-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/highlights/essai-2025-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="/assets/img/highlights/essai-2025.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded" width="100%" height="auto" alt="Talk at ESSAI 2025 in Rennes" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> <figcaption class="caption">ESSAI 2025, Rennes.</figcaption> </figure> <p>Event details: <a href="https://essai-conference.eu/">ESSAI conference website</a>.</p> <p>Paper: <a href="https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/abstract/document/10992390/">IEEE Xplore</a>.</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="highlights"/><category term="essai"/><category term="invited-talk"/><category term="model-stealing"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[I presented our SaTML paper at the European Symposium on Security and AI in Rennes.]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Winner of OCG Förderpreis 2025</title><link href="https://darusik.github.io/blog/2025/ocg-foerderpreis/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Winner of OCG Förderpreis 2025"/><published>2025-05-21T12:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2025-05-21T12:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://darusik.github.io/blog/2025/ocg-foerderpreis</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://darusik.github.io/blog/2025/ocg-foerderpreis/"><![CDATA[<p>I received the OCG Förderpreis 2025 from the Austrian Computer Society (OCG).</p> <p>The award recognizes my master’s thesis, <em>Man of Steal: Exploring Model Stealing Attacks Against Image Classifiers</em>, completed at TU Wien under the supervision of Andreas Rauber and co-supervision of Rudolf Mayer.</p> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/highlights/ocg-foerderpreis-2025-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/highlights/ocg-foerderpreis-2025-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/highlights/ocg-foerderpreis-2025-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="/assets/img/highlights/ocg-foerderpreis-2025.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded" width="100%" height="auto" alt="OCG Förderpreis 2025 announcement" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> <figcaption class="caption">OCG Förderpreis 2025.</figcaption> </figure> <p>Award details: <a href="https://www.ocg.at/fp">OCG Förderpreis</a>.</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="highlights"/><category term="award"/><category term="ocg"/><category term="ml-security"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[I received the OCG Förderpreis 2025 for my master’s thesis on model stealing attacks.]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Presenting our paper on model stealing at IEEE SaTML 2025</title><link href="https://darusik.github.io/blog/2025/new-paper-attackers-can-do-better/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Presenting our paper on model stealing at IEEE SaTML 2025"/><published>2025-04-11T12:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2025-04-11T12:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://darusik.github.io/blog/2025/new-paper-attackers-can-do-better</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://darusik.github.io/blog/2025/new-paper-attackers-can-do-better/"><![CDATA[<p>I presented our joint work with Rudolf Mayer and Andreas Rauber, <em>Attackers Can Do Better: Over- and Understated Factors of Model Stealing Attacks</em>, at IEEE SaTML 2025.</p> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/highlights/satml-2025-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/highlights/satml-2025-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/highlights/satml-2025-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="/assets/img/highlights/satml-2025.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded" width="100%" height="auto" alt="Presentation of Attackers Can Do Better at IEEE SaTML 2025" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> <figcaption class="caption">© Pia Hanfeld | IEEE SaTML 2025</figcaption> </figure> <p>Conference details: <a href="https://satml.org/2025/">IEEE SaTML 2025</a>.</p> <p>Paper: <a href="https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/abstract/document/10992390/">Attackers Can Do Better: Over- and Understated Factors of Model Stealing Attacks</a>.</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="highlights"/><category term="satml"/><category term="paper"/><category term="model-stealing"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Our SaTML 2025 paper on model stealing attacks is now published.]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Runner-up at TU Wien Informatics Awards</title><link href="https://darusik.github.io/blog/2024/tu-wien-informatics-awards-runner-up/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Runner-up at TU Wien Informatics Awards"/><published>2024-12-07T12:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2024-12-07T12:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://darusik.github.io/blog/2024/tu-wien-informatics-awards-runner-up</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://darusik.github.io/blog/2024/tu-wien-informatics-awards-runner-up/"><![CDATA[<p>I received the runner-up prize at the TU Wien Informatics Awards for my master’s thesis, <em>Man of Steal: Exploring Model Stealing Attacks Against Image Classifiers</em>.</p> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/highlights/tu-wien-informatics-awards-2025-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/highlights/tu-wien-informatics-awards-2025-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/highlights/tu-wien-informatics-awards-2025-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="/assets/img/highlights/tu-wien-informatics-awards-2025.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded" width="100%" height="auto" alt="TU Wien Informatics Awards ceremony" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> <figcaption class="caption">© Amélie Chapalain | TU Wien Informatics</figcaption> </figure> <p>Award details: <a href="https://informatics.tuwien.ac.at/informatics-awards/">TU Wien Informatics Awards</a>.</p> <p>Thesis: <a href="https://repositum.tuwien.at/handle/20.500.12708/189365">Man of steal: Exploring model stealing attacks against image classifiers</a>.</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="highlights"/><category term="award"/><category term="tu-wien"/><category term="thesis"/><category term="model-stealing"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[I received the runner-up prize for my master’s thesis at the TU Wien Informatics Awards.]]></summary></entry></feed>